<TITLE> BTTB union leader faces tax evasion charges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 2(bdnews24.com)  The National Board of Revenue Tuesday charged Firoz Mia, a union leader of Bangladesh Telegraph and Telephone Board, with tax evasion. Assistant tax commissioner of NBR Mohammad Faruqul Islam filed the case with the court of senior special judge Mohammad Azizul Huq. The judge issued an arrest warrant against Firoz. According to case details, Firoz concealed wealth amounting to Tk 2.9 crore in his income tax returns from 1986 to 2007. Firoz is already behind bars after being arrested in February in a separate case filed under the emergency powers rules. bdnews24.com/pb/mar/
